Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While the potatoes roast, put half the @Mexican style spice mix{1/2} into a large #bowl{} with a drizzle of oil. Season with salt and pepper then mix together. Lay the @British chicken breasts{2} onto your #chopping board{}, place your hand flat on top and slice into it from the side until there is 2cm left (be careful not to slice all the way through). Open it up like a book. Repeat with the other breasts. Add the chicken to the bowl of spices and turn to coat evenly all over.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}. Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice colour. While the corn cooks, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips, then chop into roughly 1cm pieces. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the sweetcorn is charred, transfer to another large bowl and wipe out your pan. Pop the (now empty) pan on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil. When hot, add the onion and pepper then season with salt and pepper. Stir-fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and remaining @Mexican style spice mix{1/2} and stir fry for ~{1%minute} more. Once cooked, transfer the veg to the sweetcorn bowl.

Pop the (now empty) pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of oil. Once hot, lay the butterflied chicken into the pan and season with salt and pepper. Cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, transfer to a #plate{} to rest for a couple of mins.

When the potatoes are cooked, put the (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat (no oil). Add the veg and potatoes to the pan and stir-fry until piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Share the hash between your plates, then slice the chicken widthways and lay on top. Finish with a dollop of @creme fraiche{75%g}. Enjoy!